name: Warung Umening MG
address: Jl. Lobong Indah, Kusamba, Kec. Dawan, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80761, Indonesia
review 1: It's not easy to get to as you have to enter from the main road a bit, but once you get there you'll be really satisfied. You will feel at ease with the owner's fluent English skills and jokes. The most important thing is that the food tastes the best.  It is clean, tasty and healthy food.  A meal enjoyed in harmony with nature in a Balinese garden.  And even a nap after dinner...You will find peace of mind at this restaurant that you cannot find in the city center of Bali.
review 2:
Delicious food and friendly owner!
Highly highly recommend best restaurant in the area!
review 3:
On my way escaping the taxis at the harbor I fortunately found this place via google.
Lovely owner speaking great english, Indonesian prices and very good food.
The husband then drove me to ubud.

It’s a little too far from the harbor by foot but totally manageable and worth the sweat. If you are in the area come by!
review 4: We had a very relaxing time laying in one of their bale bengong next to rice fields while waiting for our food. We had delicious banana with ginger smoothies and we a dish that is unforgettable and I still think about everyday is their chicken betutu!! It is by far the best chicken betutu I had in Bali, I tried finding the same at nicer restaurants and hotels, and I am now thinking how it could be possible to go there one more time for the chicken betutu. It was made using "wild/jungle chicken". One of the best tasting chickens I had overall. The woman who I believe was the owner was extremely hospitable!!
review 5: Good view with corn field beside (when I visit). I come here with my office teammate. Ayam betutu is the popular choice in this restaurant. In case someone want to go here, I also attach the picture of the price list.
